1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,972
Welcome to Befriending Your Inner Critic.

2
00:00:02,972 --> 00:00:07,931
This practice is about turning toward the
inner critic with curiosity instead of

3
00:00:07,931 --> 00:00:08,684
fighting it.

4
00:00:08,684 --> 00:00:11,378
The goal is not to let the critic take
over.

5
00:00:11,378 --> 00:00:14,443
The goal is to understand what it is
protecting.

6
00:00:14,443 --> 00:00:16,533
Begin by settling your body.

7
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:18,251
Take a slow breath in.

8
00:00:27,251 --> 00:00:27,251
<break time="3s" />

9
00:00:27,251 --> 00:00:28,598
And let it out.

10
00:00:28,598 --> 00:00:31,199
Now gently bring to mind the inner
critic.

11
00:00:31,199 --> 00:00:32,499
Notice its voice.

12
00:00:32,499 --> 00:00:33,567
Its tone.

13
00:00:33,567 --> 00:00:35,610
Its favorite messages.

14
00:00:35,610 --> 00:00:38,211
Its posture or image, if it has one.

15
00:00:38,211 --> 00:00:39,697
Do not argue with it yet.

16
00:00:39,697 --> 00:00:41,137
Just notice it.

17
00:00:41,137 --> 00:00:45,688
Ask: Where do I sense this critic in or
around my body?

18
00:00:57,688 --> 00:00:57,688
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

19
00:00:57,688 --> 00:01:00,707
Now ask: How do I feel toward this
critic?

20
00:01:12,707 --> 00:01:12,707
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

21
00:01:12,707 --> 00:01:18,187
If you feel angry, ashamed, afraid, or
exhausted, that makes sense.

22
00:01:18,187 --> 00:01:21,856
See if those reactions can give you a
little space so you can listen.

23
00:01:39,856 --> 00:01:39,856
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

24
00:01:39,856 --> 00:01:45,275
Now say to the critic: I know you may be
trying to help. I am not here to let you

25
00:01:45,275 --> 00:01:48,865
hurt me. I am here to understand why you
work so hard.

26
00:01:48,865 --> 00:01:54,345
Ask the critic: What are you afraid would
happen if you stopped criticizing me?

27
00:02:06,345 --> 00:02:06,345
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

28
00:02:06,345 --> 00:02:07,413
Listen.

29
00:02:25,413 --> 00:02:25,413
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

30
00:02:25,413 --> 00:02:30,776
Maybe it fears failure, rejection,
humiliation, abandonment, loss of

31
00:02:30,776 --> 00:02:35,258
control, being seen, being too much, or
not being enough.

32
00:02:35,258 --> 00:02:40,599
Now ask: Who or what taught you that
criticism was necessary?

33
00:02:52,599 --> 00:02:52,599
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

34
00:02:52,599 --> 00:02:53,992
Listen gently.

35
00:02:53,992 --> 00:02:56,128
You do not need a full memory.

36
00:02:56,128 --> 00:02:57,707
Just notice what comes.

37
00:02:57,707 --> 00:03:00,865
Now ask: What are you trying to make me
become?

38
00:03:12,865 --> 00:03:12,865
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

39
00:03:12,865 --> 00:03:16,116
And: What are you trying to prevent me
from becoming?

40
00:03:28,116 --> 00:03:28,116
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

41
00:03:28,116 --> 00:03:30,299
Notice the protective intention.

42
00:03:30,299 --> 00:03:34,479
The critic may be harsh because it
believes harshness keeps you safe.

43
00:03:34,479 --> 00:03:39,638
Now say: I understand that you are trying
to protect me. I also need a different

44
00:03:39,638 --> 00:03:44,928
way. Would you be willing to try speaking
to me with more honesty and less attack?

45
00:03:56,928 --> 00:03:56,928
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

46
00:03:56,928 --> 00:03:58,786
Notice the response.

47
00:03:58,786 --> 00:04:02,548
If the critic is unwilling, ask what it
needs first.

48
00:04:02,548 --> 00:04:05,799
If it is willing, invite it to rephrase
one message.

49
00:04:05,799 --> 00:04:10,825
For example, instead of “You are a
failure,” it might say, “I am scared you

50
00:04:10,825 --> 00:04:12,115
will be rejected.”.

51
00:04:12,115 --> 00:04:18,617
Instead of “You are too much,” it might
say, “I am afraid people will leave.”.

52
00:04:18,617 --> 00:04:23,308
Instead of “You must be perfect,” it
might say, “I need reassurance that

53
00:04:23,308 --> 00:04:25,026
mistakes are survivable.”.

54
00:04:25,026 --> 00:04:28,045
Now thank the critic for revealing what
is underneath.

55
00:04:28,045 --> 00:04:32,782
Ask: What would help you trust
Self-energy more?

56
00:04:44,782 --> 00:04:44,782
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

57
00:04:44,782 --> 00:04:45,804
Listen.

58
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:03,804
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

59
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:06,033
Take a slow breath in.

60
00:05:15,033 --> 00:05:15,033
<break time="3s" />

61
00:05:15,033 --> 00:05:16,566
And let it out.

62
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:20,508
Let the critic know you will keep
listening, but you will also practice

63
00:05:20,508 --> 00:05:21,860
leading with compassion.

64
00:05:21,860 --> 00:05:23,625
Return gently to the room.

